Basic filesystem & permissions

ls -lah, cd /path, pwd, mkdir -p foo, rm -rf foo
cp -r, mv, stat file, file file
chmod u+x script.sh, chmod 644 file, chown user:group file


Process & services

ps aux | grep <name>
top / htop
systemctl status ssh, journalctl -u <svc>
kill <pid>, kill -9 <pid>
Package management (Debian/Ubuntu/Kali)
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y <package>


Networking basics

ip a (interfaces), ip route (routes)
ss -tuln (listening sockets), ss -tnp (TCP connections + PID)
netstat -tnlp (if installed)
arp -a, ping <ip>, traceroute <ip>
tcpdump -i any -n -s 0 -w capture.pcap (requires sudo)
tshark -r capture.pcap -T fields -e ... (analyze)


File transfer & simple servers

python3 -m http.server 8000 (serve directory)
nc -l -p 4444 (netcat listener) / nc <ip> 4444 (connect)


Log inspection

tail -f /var/log/syslog
less /var/log/auth.log
grep -E "ERROR|Failed|Denied" /var/log/*.log
